WEBVTT

00:04.638 --> 00:06.171
Fargo.

00:06.173 --> 00:08.474
<i>All new Wednesdays at 10:00.</i>

00:08.476 --> 00:10.843
<i>Starts April 19 on FX.</i>

00:12.178 --> 00:14.246
<i>FX presents</i> The Americans.

00:18.451 --> 00:20.052
<i>Previously on "The Americans"...</i>

00:24.791 --> 00:27.059
We need to talk
in private... soon.

00:29.696 --> 00:31.630
<i>She's working for us.</i>

00:31.632 --> 00:33.465
You remember three years ago,

00:33.467 --> 00:35.801
when that KGB officer
was killed?

00:35.803 --> 00:37.202
<i>I</i> shot him.

00:37.204 --> 00:42.007
If the CIA uses the tape
I made to blackmail Burov,

00:42.009 --> 00:43.042
I will go public.

00:43.044 --> 00:45.144
So, I have interview tomorrow.

00:45.146 --> 00:46.512
That's great.

00:46.514 --> 00:50.049
If she gets a job
teaching Russian at the CIA...

00:50.051 --> 00:51.483
There's a chance we could get

00:51.485 --> 00:53.519
every officer they're training

00:53.521 --> 00:54.720
for Moscow.

00:59.059 --> 01:01.260
His mother defected,
he got himself arrested,

01:01.262 --> 01:04.229
and now he's come here to see
a father he's never met.

01:04.230 --> 01:06.098
You don't trust Philip.

01:06.100 --> 01:08.500
He already has
entries in his file

01:08.502 --> 01:10.169
that don't look good.

01:10.171 --> 01:11.737
He's his son.

01:13.173 --> 01:14.673
I want see father.

01:14.675 --> 01:19.011
It would put him
in terrible danger.

01:20.280 --> 01:22.481
You cannot see him.

01:30.056 --> 01:33.092
But then, what was Morozov doing
at that greenhouse?

01:33.094 --> 01:35.461
They're using strains of wheat
from all over the world,

01:35.463 --> 01:39.264
and no one knows more
about Soviet wheat than Morozov.

01:39.266 --> 01:43.235
And Stobert just wants to end
world hunger...

01:43.237 --> 01:45.471
Like miss America.

01:45.473 --> 01:46.839
Jesus.

01:48.708 --> 01:53.312
So, the laboratory worker...
How's Philip taking it?

01:53.314 --> 01:54.379
He'll be fine.

01:54.381 --> 01:57.282
How's he taking it, Elizabeth?

01:57.284 --> 01:59.084
The same as me...
It's upsetting.

01:59.086 --> 02:00.385
For me, too.

02:04.124 --> 02:08.092
Well, if they've come up with
some kind of super wheat,

02:08.095 --> 02:10.729
think what getting our hands
on it could mean to us.

02:10.731 --> 02:12.297
No more shortages.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.967
No more buying grain
from the west.

02:14.969 --> 02:17.469
We could make it right.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.738
In that greenhouse,
everything was dying

02:19.740 --> 02:21.173
except right in the middle.

02:21.175 --> 02:23.742
There was
this strong, healthy wheat.

02:23.744 --> 02:25.277
Good.

02:25.279 --> 02:27.479
That's good.
We'll start there.

02:27.481 --> 02:30.149
Why don't we get photographs
of the greenhouse?

02:30.151 --> 02:32.518
Make sure nothing has changed.

02:32.520 --> 02:34.820
I'll get it taken care of.

02:34.822 --> 02:37.356
You two stay
with Stobert and Kemp.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.433
I'm sorry you're spread so thin.

02:48.435 --> 02:50.002
It's...

02:52.772 --> 02:54.673
it's part of the job, I know.

02:56.809 --> 02:58.243
But now...

03:04.384 --> 03:07.386
Is something wrong with me?

03:09.056 --> 03:10.689
It's a long career.

03:12.859 --> 03:17.262
And there is nothing wrong
with you... ever.

03:23.303 --> 03:25.370
Here.

03:25.372 --> 03:27.239
This one will be easy.

03:29.842 --> 03:31.243
Are <i> you</i> all right?

03:32.545 --> 03:34.880
Oh, yes.

03:34.882 --> 03:37.749
I'm just tired.

03:37.751 --> 03:39.218
And old.

